annotationA: Inositol polyphosphate 5-phosphatase E; Converts phosphatidylinositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate (PtdIns 3,4,5-P3) to PtdIns-P2, and phosphatidylinositol 4,5- bisphosphate (PtdIns 4,5-P2) to phosphatidylinositol 4-phosphate (PI-4-P). By controlling the phosphoinositide composition of the cilia membrane of auditory receptor neurons, regulates the cilia localization of ktub and consequently the transient receptor potential channels iav and nompC; Belongs to the inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate 5- phosphatase type IV family
annotationB: Pi4KIIalpha, isoform A; Pi4KIIalpha is a lipid kinase that synthesizes phosphatidylinositol 4-phosphate from phosphatidylinositol. Pi4KIIalpha contributes to membrane trafficking in the larval salivary gland
